list.item:
4 Of the Inuisibility of the Romane Church,
for more then 500 yeeres next after Christ,
page 54.

div.p:
The Church may be considered
Either in respect of election & inward sanctification;
Or in respect of outward vocation, and profession of the truth.

Such as subscribe to the harmony of Protestant
Confessions, in each point of faith
and Theologicall Conclusion;

The most cunning Work-man that euer▪ wrought with the tools of naturall wit, forceth all Arguments into two kindes;
〈 in non-Latin alphabet 〉 or reprehensorie.
〈 in non-Latin alphabet 〉 or demonstratiue.

That there is a Treasury of Saints merits,
and superaboundant satisfactions at
the Pope's disposing;

Is not this iust like Battus his spell in the Latin Poet;
—Subillis
Montibus, inquit, erant, et erant sub montibus illis:
